  <body>
    <div class="bg-layer"></div>
    <div class="bg-grid"></div>

    <header class="legal-nav">
      <a href="/" class="back-btn">
        <i class="ri-arrow-left-line"></i>
        Back Home
      </a>
    </header>

    <div class="legal-brand">
      <img src="/images/LinkForge.png" alt="LinkForge" />
    </div>

    <div class="legal-container">
      <h1>About LinkForge</h1>
      <p class="legal-badge">About Our Platform</p>
      <p class="legal-subtitle">LinkForge is a link management tool built for people who share links regularly and want to keep things clean, trackable, and simple.</p>

      <!-- WHAT IT IS -->
      <h2>What is LinkForge?</h2>
      <p>
        LinkForge is a URL shortener with built-in analytics and QR code generation. You paste a long URL, get a short shareable link, and can track how many times it's been clicked — all
        from one dashboard.
      </p>
      <p>
        It was built as a project to solve a real problem: long URLs are ugly, hard to share, and give you no information about engagement. LinkForge fixes that without requiring
        any complex setup.
      </p>

      <!-- WHAT IT DOES — feature cards -->
      <h2>What You Can Do</h2>

      <div class="about-features">
        <div class="about-feature-card">
          <div class="about-feature-icon">
            <i class="ri-link"></i>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Shorten URLs</h3>
            <p>Turn any long URL into a clean short link. Copy and share it anywhere — social media, emails, printed materials.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-feature-card">
          <div class="about-feature-icon">
            <i class="ri-bar-chart-2-line"></i>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Track Clicks</h3>
            <p>Every click on your short link is logged with a timestamp. See total clicks per link directly from your dashboard.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-feature-card">
          <div class="about-feature-icon">
            <i class="ri-qr-code-line"></i>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Generate QR Codes</h3>
            <p>Every short link automatically gets a QR code. Download it as a PNG and use it on posters, business cards, or anywhere offline.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-feature-card">
          <div class="about-feature-icon">
            <i class="ri-shield-check-line"></i>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Secure Accounts</h3>
            <p>Email verification and OTP-based password reset keep your account protected. Google OAuth is also supported for quick sign-in.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- WHO IT'S FOR -->
      <h2>Who It's For</h2>
      <p>LinkForge is useful for anyone who regularly shares links and wants more control over them. That includes:</p>

      <div class="about-tags">
        <span class="about-tag">Content creators</span>
        <span class="about-tag">Students & developers</span>
        <span class="about-tag">Small businesses</span>
        <span class="about-tag">Marketers</span>
        <span class="about-tag">Anyone sharing links in bios or posts</span>
        <span class="about-tag">Offline campaign managers</span>
      </div>

      <!-- LEGAL LINKS -->
      <h2>Legal</h2>
      <p>Read our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> to understand how we handle your data, and our <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a> for usage guidelines.</p>

      <!-- CONTACT -->
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>Questions, feedback, or bug reports:</p>

      <a class="legal-email" href="https://mail.google.com/mail/?view=cm&fs=1&to=support@linkforge.com" target="_blank"> support@linkforge.com </a>

      <hr class="legal-divider" />
      <p class="legal-footer">© 2026 LinkForge. All rights reserved.</p>
    </div>
